\f1\b0 Change History\
1.0 - 10 November 2005 - Original release\
\
EventMonitorTest is a sample to show how a process can get notified of keyboard, mouse and tablet events while the process is in the background. This notification is possible using the 
\f2\fs20 \CocoaLigature0 GetEventMonitorTarget 
\f1\fs24 \CocoaLigature1 to monitor inputs across all processes. 
\f2\fs20 \CocoaLigature0 GetEventMonitorTarget
\f1\fs24 \CocoaLigature1   is available in Mac OS X 10.3.x and greater.  The use of 
\f2\fs20 \CocoaLigature0 GetEventMonitorTarget
\f1\fs24 \CocoaLigature1 allows for event notification only. A process cannot filter incoming events destined to other processes using the 
\f2\fs20 \CocoaLigature0 GetEventMonitorTarget
\f1\fs24 \CocoaLigature1 mechanism.\
\
The sample is compiled in Universal Binary format.\
